                   /General information/                          7925 1451
                                                                  7925 1451
 Neutron average resonance parameters Sn0, Sn1, Sn2, and R' were  7925 1451
obtained so as to reproduce the absorption, and shape elastic     7925 1451
cross sections of the DCCOM potential RIPL1843 by Capote et al.,  7925 1451
described in NDS 110 (2009) 3107-3214. The capture parameters     7925 1451
(capture transmission coefficients at zero energy and different   7925 1451
parity) were determined in a fit to the gold Standard capture     7925 1451
cross section evaluation as given by ENDF/B-VII.1, NSUB=19(Std),  7925 1451
IAEA-CRP&NEA-WPEC(SG7)&CSEWG. The Standard evaluation is based on 7925 1451
the GMA code and described in NDS 110 (2009) 3215-3324.           7925 1451
 A small background cross section was introduced into MF/MT=3/102 7925 1451
from 3.75 to 11.75 keV at the expense of MF/MT=3/2 in order to    7925 1451
make the evaluated smooth statistical capture cross section curve 7925 1451
locally identical to the GMA Standard one. The latter agrees      7925 1451
slightly better with the LSD benchmark only in that region.       7925 1451
 At the 5 keV point the capture cross section of ENDF/B-VII.1     7925 1451
(and RRDF-2008) is about 1% higher than the one of the present    7925 1451
file and the Standard, due to improper "linear-linear" instead of 7925 1451
"log-log" interpolation of the Standard by ENDF/B-VII.1 at this   7925 1451
point.                                                            7925 1451
 In comparison of the total cross sections from 5 to 20 keV,      7925 1451
ENDF/B-VII.1 is substantially (up to 15%) lower than the present  7925 1451
file and the DCCOM, since ENDF/B-VII.1 follows the older data by  7925 1451
Seth (1958) disregarding the Purtov (1994) data, which are close  7925 1451
to the recent measurements at GELINA.                             7925 1451
 Measures were taken to reduce the non-Hauser-Feshbach processing 7925 1451
for the Jpi sequences (1+, 2+) of double-orbital contribution by  7925 1451
using the flexibility of the format. As known, the above short-   7925 1451
coming is due to the ENDF-6 simplifying, but anti-Hauser-Feshbach 7925 1451
assumption for orbital momentum conservation. The latter removes  7925 1451
the competition e.g. of the s-wave elastic channel for the above  7925 1451
d-wave reactions. The effect for gold at 100 keV reaches a 10%    7925 1451
increase in the capture cross section. To solve the problem, a    7925 1451
a reduction/adjustment of the corresponding d-wave reaction       7925 1451
widths can be used. The total cross section remains intact in     7925 1451
such a procedure, so that the elastic one gets also corrected.    7925 1451
Even the simplest remedy demonstrated in the file, as a zero      7925 1451
iteration to adapt the corresponding d-wave reaction widths,      7925 1451
diminished the above effect to -3%. The results were compared     7925 1451
making use of the IRMM URR code, which can process both ways - by 7925 1451
sticking to the ENDF-6 model with and without the assumption for  7925 1451
L-conservation.                                                   7925 1451
